<p>Does the following code logic cause the original call's stack frame to contain the memory from each subsequent call (causing excessive memory usage)?</p>  <pre><code>function foo (arg) {     bar(arg); }  function bar (arg) {   $.ajax({      success: function (data) {          if (data['result'] == 'continue') {             bar(data['nextarg']);          } else if (data['result'] == 'done') {             alert('done!');          }      }   }); } </code></pre>